The new infections were found after the analysis of 3,935 samples in the past 24 hours. 

CS Kagwe said 146 of the patients were Kenyans and 48 foreigners, 108 male and 86 female, the youngest six years old and the oldest 95. 










 

Nairobi County accounted for 132 of the new infections and was followed by Kiambu with nine, Meru with seven, Kisumu and Kilifi with six each and Laikipia five. 

Mombasa and Kajiado counties each had four new Covid-19 cases while Nakuru, Turkana, Uasin Gishu and Machakos had three each. 



