Kisii county reported two case while Lamu, Murang’a, Nandi, Taita Taveta, Trans Nzoia, Busia and Embu had just one new case each. 

The ministry also announced that the number of recovered patients in Kenya had increased by 39 to 85,665. Thirty six of them had been hospitalized while three were under the home-based care programme. 










 

As of Tuesday, the Health ministry’s records showed that 344 patients had been admitted to health facilities countywide while 1,283 were being treated at home. 

Of those in hospital, 55 were in intensive care units (ICU), 26 of them on ventilatory support, 23 on supplemental oxygen and six under observation. 

Nine other patients were also on supplementary oxygen but in the general wards. 



